data.enText: a list of items to be discussed at a meeting

data.chText: 议程表上的下一项是宣传预算。
data.enText: The next item on the agenda is the publicity budget.

data.chText: 对政府来说，现在教育是当务之急。
data.enText: For the government, education is now at the top of the agenda (= most important) .

data.chText: 我们公司高度重视质量。
data.enText: In our company, quality is high on the agenda .

data.chText: 人们指责报章企图替政府决定政务的轻重缓急。
data.enText: Newspapers have been accused of trying to set the agenda for the government (= decide what is important) .

data.chText: 记事簿用diary或datebook（北美英语），不用agenda。记录约见等事宜也可用台历或挂历（calendar）。diary或journal亦指日记、日志：
data.enText: A book with a space for each day where you write down things that you have to do in the future is called a diary or a datebook ( NAmE ) (not an agenda ). You may also have a calendar on your desk or hanging up in your room, where you write down your appointments. A diary or a journal is also the record that some people keep of what has happened during the day.

data.chText: 在英国英语中，schedule指工作计划、日程安排，timetable指时间表、时刻表：
data.enText: In BrE your schedule is a plan that lists all the work that you have to do and when you must do each thing and a timetable is a list showing the fixed times at which events will happen.

data.chText: 公共汽车 / 火车时刻表
在北美英语中，上述两种含义均用schedule。
data.enText: In NAmE these are both called a schedule .

simple_means.memory_skill: ag 做；代理；引导 + enda 表示名词多数 → 做的事情 → 议程

ex.chText: 他安排了一个紧凑的旅行日程。
ex.enText: He has planned a tight travel schedule.

ex.chText: 你已经安排了考试日程吗?
ex.enText: Have you made the examination schedule?
The project was completed ahead of schedule.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事的计划及具体运作的时间表。

ex.chText: 我们必须将这件事提上议事日程。
ex.enText: We must put this item on the agenda.

ex.chText: 会议主席说今天下午有一长串待议事项。
ex.enText: The chairman says there is a lengthy agenda this afternoon.

synonyms.bx: 主要指会议上需要商议解决的问题的一览表。

ex.chText: 他的个人日程表上记着5月5日有个约会。
ex.enText: There is a notation about an appointment on his personal calendar for May 5.

ex.chText: 依照大学的日程表，你们的考试将在7月举行。
ex.enText: According to the university calendar your examinations will be in July.

ex.chText: 总统选举是明年政治日程表上的大事。
ex.enText: The presidential election is the highlight of next year's political calendar.

synonyms.bx: 指某人在记事簿上记下的要做各项事情的计划，也指某个团体或某项活动一年内重大事件的日程安排。

ex.chText: 第一份航空时刻表是在1928年由泛美航空公司刊印的。
ex.enText: The first airplane timetable was published by Pan-American Airways in 1928.

ex.chText: 我这星期的时间安排很紧。
ex.enText: I've got a very busy timetable this week.

ex.chText: 大雾打乱了他们的旅行日程。
ex.enText: The heavy fog upset their timetable for the trip.

synonyms.bx: 比 schedule 更为具体，常指车、船、航班等的时刻表，也指课程表或活动计划的时间表。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：时间表，计划表

tr: a temporally organized plan for matters to be attended to
a list of matters to be taken up (as at a meeting)

value.def: You can refer to the political issues which are important at a particular time as an agenda.

example.ex: Does television set the agenda on foreign policy?...
example.tran: 电视舆论对外交政策有影响吗？

example.ex: Many of the coalition members could have their own political agendas...
example.tran: 许多联盟成员可能会有他们自己的政治议题。

example.ex: The Danish president will put environmental issues high on the agenda.
example.tran: 丹麦总统将试图把环境问题摆到重要位置上。

value.def: An agenda is a list of the items that have to be discussed at a meeting.

example.ex: This is sure to be an item on the agenda next week...
example.tran: 这一定会成为下星期议事日程上的一项议题。

example.ex: High on the agenda of tomorrow's meeting will be the turmoil in Japan.
example.tran: 日本发生的骚乱将是明天会议的首要议题。
